<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Crimsonjade</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-13 17:38:36</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>this is for all those people who dont play on blue servers.  the fact that roughly half of the rods are in dark controlled areas and the other half are in light controlled areas makes some of the rods tedious to get.  i used invis most of the time and removed any items that could be seen on my body.  review the enemy zones beore u enter them and keep that internal timer running so you can set yourself up in a safe spot to recast invis without jeopardizing your health/mana.  im 24 and used my gates to their full advantage.  i have found all the rods except the guk one without incident.  though i would have had problems with the zombie sailors, in eruds crossing, if i was a little lower.  but my point is that the hard part of the quest is the obtaining the rod in lower guk.  if you have never been there its easy to get lost.  the rod is on the dead side of lower guk and the vampire bats arent dead so the invis vs. undead trick wont work.  my advice is to wait until the place is swarming with people.  if your on a pvp server and light like me hopefully you will only run into darks that are OOR.  then just carefully weave your way through the tunnel maze until you find the hand room.  hopefully its occupied and u can get it in between spawns.  else u might be able (if ur ballsy and high enough) train the hand and such quick and go back and look for it in a frenzy.  good luck</font></td></tr></table>
