<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Ok Call me lucky but I started this quest this morning. I completely dreaded the idea of having to go to erud's crossing, cause of  all the horror storys I have read about it on all the diff msg boards.  At anyrate, when I got to Erud's crossing I bound, took off all my gear, and had a friend kill me so I would not loose everything to these terrible nasty wizard eating sharks. Any way I took a hit off of a water stone and dove in! Swam over the boat down the slope and ran smack dab into the rod picked it up and swam back ... It was so amazing... No sharks I mean at ALL. I must have just gotten lucky but I  sat just below the water line and looked around and saw no sharks in the area... So I guess the moral of this story is requardless who you listen too, or who or what kills you... you will die at least once in Erud's crossing :P   IN all honesty guys I think the hardest rod to get is the one in LGuk I Started the quest at about 11 am ish and had all rods by 2 pm all except the guk one... when I went to bed at 2 am I still did not have it and had died 4 times.. ( Gotta love GIBS)  oh yea and I am lvl 32 if it helps <BR>
